# HLA x celiac sanity check

Loaded 535658 people from the HLA-calls TSV; 535658 have a phenotype label (3254 cases, 532404 controls).

## (A) Positive-control check -- celiac

Risk marker: DQ2.5 (DQA1*05:01+DQB1*02:01) or DQ8 (DQA1*03:01+DQB1*03:02) carrier, unphased presence (standard clinical-typing convention -- both cis- and trans-configured DQ2.5 confer risk, and AoU-native calls are not phased across genes anyway)

| Group | n | carrier+case | carrier+ctrl | non-carrier+case | non-carrier+ctrl | OR | Fisher p |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| ALL (pooled) | 535658 | 2176 | 208603 | 1078 | 323801 | 3.13 | 1.486e-221 |
| afr | 100798 | 43 | 23951 | 95 | 76709 | 1.45 | 4.559e-02 |
| amr | 107928 | 178 | 52519 | 107 | 55124 | 1.75 | 4.352e-06 |
| eas | 15893 | 10 | 3734 | 18 | 12131 | 1.80 | 1.775e-01 |
| eur | 302712 | 1927 | 125559 | 849 | 174377 | 3.15 | 7.286e-187 |
| mid | 2151 | 9 | 853 | 1 | 1288 | 13.59 | 1.668e-03 |
| sas | 6176 | 9 | 1987 | 8 | 4172 | 2.36 | 1.152e-01 |

## (B) Untargeted check -- L1 logistic regression over ALL alleles, all 8 genes

No disease-specific hints given to the model -- features are every 2-field allele seen at each of the 8 classical genes (dosage 0/1/2), plus ancestry dummies for population-stratification adjustment.

Rows used: 535649 (3254 cases / 532395 controls). Features: 2379 (allele dosages + ancestry dummies).

### (B1) Generalization -- 5-fold cross-validated, out-of-fold predictions

Every number below comes from predictions on people NOT used to train that prediction -- this is the actual answer to "does it generalize," not the coefficient inspection in (B2) below.

Pooled AUROC: 0.740 | Pooled AUPRC: 0.021 (baseline/prevalence = 0.607%) -- AUPRC matters more than AUROC here given how rare the outcome is; plain accuracy is not reported because predicting "nobody has it" already scores 99.4%.

**Risk-decile enrichment** (rank-based bins -- decile 1 = highest predicted risk)

| Decile | n | observed case rate | enrichment vs baseline |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | 53565 | 2.294% | 3.8x |
| 2 | 53565 | 1.027% | 1.7x |
| 3 | 53565 | 0.597% | 1.0x |
| 4 | 53565 | 0.521% | 0.9x |
| 5 | 53565 | 0.450% | 0.7x |
| 6 | 53565 | 0.428% | 0.7x |
| 7 | 53565 | 0.267% | 0.4x |
| 8 | 53565 | 0.196% | 0.3x |
| 9 | 53565 | 0.170% | 0.3x |
| 10 | 53564 | 0.125% | 0.2x |

**Threshold metrics** (flagging the top X% by predicted risk as "high-risk")

| Threshold | n flagged | PPV | Sensitivity | Specificity | NPV |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| top 5% | 26782 | 2.86% | 23.54% | 95.11% | 99.51% |
| top 10% | 53565 | 2.29% | 37.77% | 90.17% | 99.58% |

**Per-ancestry generalization** (same OOF predictions, evaluated within each group; groups with fewer than 10 cases or 10 controls are flagged as insufficient rather than given a number that would just be noise)

| Ancestry | n | cases | AUROC | AUPRC | top-10%-within-group PPV | sensitivity |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| afr | 100798 | 138 | 0.542 | 0.002 | 0.20% | 14.49% |
| amr | 107926 | 285 | 0.606 | 0.005 | 0.60% | 22.81% |
| eas | 15892 | 28 | 0.595 | 0.003 | 0.25% | 14.29% |
| eur | 302706 | 2776 | 0.681 | 0.023 | 2.80% | 30.55% |
| mid | 2151 | 10 | 0.763 | 0.014 | 1.40% | 30.00% |
| sas | 6176 | 17 | 0.691 | 0.008 | 0.81% | 29.41% |

### (B2) What the model learned -- one fit on all data, for interpretation only

Not a performance claim (see (B1) above for that) -- this just asks whether the model, given zero disease-specific hints, lands on real biology.

Non-zero coefficients after L1 shrinkage: 833 / 2379

#### Top 15 risk-associated features (positive coefficient = higher odds)

| Feature | Coefficient | Odds ratio (approx, per copy) |
|---|---|---|
| DQB1*02:01 | 0.205 | 1.23 |
